                    <comment id="12758973" author="john.wang@gmail.com" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 03:08:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;this is a stand-alone class&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12759077" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 10:57:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks great John, thanks.  Where would you put it?  contrib/misc maybe?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12759108" author="john.wang@gmail.com" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 14:03:04 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I had put them in the core package under org.apache.lucene.index.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because it requires access package protected classes, e.g. SegmentInfo, it needs to be in that package.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In terms of which module, totally up to you as you would know what the best place to put it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A question on the side, MergePolicy is something the API suggests that is customizable, yet SegmentInfo, part of the signature is package protected. Is this something should be opened up to allow for full customization of MergePolicy amonst other things?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-John&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12759129" author="mikemccand" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 15:20:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve opened up SegmentInfo/s in 2.9.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12759132" author="john.wang@gmail.com" created="Thu, 24 Sep 2009 15:31:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Awesome, didn&apos;t realize!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-John&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="12760751" author="mikemccand" created="Tue, 29 Sep 2009 23:34:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Trivial formatting changes, basic javadoc, and moved to contrib/misc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
